<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,649,1216]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,865,891]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[838,983,866,892]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shalaby, F." box="[1024,1196,866,893]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="339 - 342" refId="ref40040" refString="Shalaby, F. (1962) Contribution to the insect fauna of Saudi Arabia. Bulletin of the Entomological Society of Egypt, 46, 339 - 342." type="journal article" year="1962">Shalaby (1962)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1232,1380,866,892]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphaerophoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menthastri">
<emphasis box="[1232,1380,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">S. menthastri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.), while 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, H. E." box="[220,377,902,928]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref37604" refString="Martin, H. E. (1972) Report to the Government of Saudi Arabia on Research in Plant Protection, based on the work of H. E. Martin. FAO entomologist, Rome, 38 pp." type="book" year="1972">Martin (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Abu-Thuraya, N. H." box="[428,660,902,928]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref32975" refString="Abu-Thuraya, N. H. (1982) General Survey, Agricultural in Saudi Arabia. Ministry of Agriculture and Water. Agriculture Research Department of Plant Protection, Academic Publishing &amp; Press, Ministry of Agriculture and Water, Riyadh, 326 pp." type="book" year="1982">Abu-Thuraya (1982)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bankowska, 1964" authorityName="in Bankowska" authorityYear="1964" box="[822,1185,902,928]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphaerophoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turkmenica">
<emphasis box="[822,975,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">S. turkmenica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bankowska, R." box="[982,1185,902,928]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="285 - 353" refId="ref33423" refString="Bankowska, R. (1964) Studien uber die palaarktischen Arten der Gattung Spaerophoria St. Farg. Et Serv. (Diptera: Syrphidae). Annales Zoologici Instytut Zoologiczny, Polska Akademia Nauk. Warszawa, 22 (15), 285 - 353." type="journal article" year="1964">Bańkowska, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,938,964]" name="India" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">India</collectingCountry>
(Bengale) and is further recorded from the Palaearctic Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[936,1076,938,964]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1136,938,964]" name="Iran" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Iran</collectingCountry>
, Caucasus (North), 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1432,938,964]" name="China" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,974,1000]" name="South Korea" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[278,345,974,1000]" name="Japan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[354,512,974,1000]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
; Oriental Region: 
<collectingCountry box="[714,774,974,1000]" name="India" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[784,854,974,1000]" name="Nepal" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[864,962,974,1000]" name="Pakistan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[971,1049,974,1000]" country="Pakistan" name="Punjab" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Punjab</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peck, L. V." box="[1062,1183,974,1000]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref38699" refString="Peck, L. V. (1988) Family Syrphidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Syrphidae- Conopidae. Vol. 8. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 11 - 230." type="book" year="1988">Peck 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Subhan, F. &amp; Shah, M." box="[1194,1432,974,1000]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1192 - 1198" refId="ref40658" refString="Subhan, F. &amp; Shah, M. (2016) Taxonomic study of genus Sphaerophoria Le Peletier et Serville (Diptera: Syrphidae) with three species from Northern Dry Mountains region of Pakistan. Journal of Entomology and Zoology Studies, 4 (4), 1192 - 1198." type="journal article" year="2016">Subhan &amp; Shah 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghorpade, K." box="[151,328,1010,1036]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="3 - 13" refId="ref35835" refString="Ghorpade, K. (2009) Freidberg, A. (1988) Some nomenclatural notes on Indian Subregion Syrphini (Diptera: Syrphidae). Colemani, 15, 3 - 13." type="journal article" year="2009">Ghorpadé 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghorpade, K." box="[340,400,1010,1036]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref35870" refString="Ghorpade, K. (2014) An updated Check-list of the Hover-flies (Diptera: Syrphidae) recorded in the Indian subcontinent. Colemania, 44, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sengupta, J. &amp; Naskar, A. &amp; Maity, A. &amp; Hazra, S. &amp; Mukhopadhyay, E. &amp; Banerjee, D. &amp; Ghosh, S." box="[411,648,1010,1037]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="381 - 396" refId="ref39972" refString="Sengupta, J., Naskar, A., Maity, A., Hazra, S., Mukhopadhyay, E., Banerjee, D. &amp; Ghosh, S. (2016) An updated distributional account of Indian Hover flies (insect: Diptera: Syrphidae). Journal of Entomology and Zoology, 4 (6), 381 - 396." type="journal article" year="2016">
Sengupta 
<emphasis box="[523,573,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Arabian Peninsula this species recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1255,1323,1010,1036]" name="Oman" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Oman</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,1010,1036]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">UAE</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, J. T. &amp; van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R." box="[159,344,1046,1072]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref40237" refString="Smit, J. T., van Harten, A. &amp; Ketelaar, R. (2017) Order Diptera, family Syrphidae the hoverflies of the Arabian Peninsula. In: van Harten, A. (Eds.), Arthropod fauna of the UAE. Vol. 6. Department of the President's Affairs, Abu Dhabi, pp. 572 - 612." type="book" year="2017">
Smit 
<emphasis box="[220,270,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
